{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88c6848b-1455-4907-90b9-a3d2c284d361","content":"## MSTest v3 `.testsettings` Migration\n\nMSTest v3 **no longer supports `.testsettings` files**. You need to replace it with a `.runsettings` file and MSTest configuration in your project.\n\nHere's how to migrate the three things your `local.testsettings` configures:\n\n### 1. Create a `.runsettings` file\n\nThis replaces the timeout and code coverage data collector:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <RunConfiguration>\n    <TestSessionTimeout>30000</TestSessionTimeout>\n  </RunConfiguration>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n                     uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n### 2. Update your `.csproj` to reference it\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Delete `local.testsettings`\n\nIt's no longer read by the test platform.\n\n---\n\n**Key differences:**\n- **Timeout** → `<TestTimeout>` in `<MSTest>` section (per-test) or `[Timeout(ms)]` attribute\n- **Deployment/AssemblyResolution** → `<DeploymentEnabled>` in `<MSTest>` (usually `false` in SDK-style projects since the build output directory is used directly)\n- **Code Coverage** → `<DataCollectors>` in `<DataCollectionRunSettings>`\n\nWould you like me to create the `.runsettings` file and update the project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dcdc13d6-eb99-43a8-8965-24a879167d72","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"BD02:158C5C:2073BD4:24CD8F9:6A07D9D2"},"id":"9a52da89-386e-475b-8bab-6a8b642a7872","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:43:40.651Z","parentId":"6643f00a-f83a-4cc8-8c1e-13729499d979"}
